  "text": "Immunohistochemistry and analysis. Immunohistochemical staining was carried out on deparaffinized and rehydrated tissue sections from formalin-fixed, paraffin-embedded blocks or tissue microarrays (TMA). Immunohistochemistry for NY-ESO-1 (encoded by CTAG1B gene) and MAGEA1 was done with the EnVision+ kit (DakoCytomation). For NY-ESO-1, slides were steamed for 20 min in 1Â citrate unmasking solution (Vector Labs) for antigen retrieval and then incubated with anti-NY-ESO-1 primary antibodies (1:100 dilution; Zymed) for 45 min at room temperature. For MAGEA1, slides were steamed in 1 Â EDTA buffer (Zymed) for 40 min and stained with anti-MAGEA1 primary antibody (1:100 dilution; Zymed) at room temperature for 45 min. Immunohistochemistry with anti5me C antibody was done with the Power Vision+ detection system (Immunovision Technologies). Antigen retrieval was accomplished by steaming slides for 20 min in citrate unmasking solution and then treating with 3.5 N HCl for 15 min. Slides were then stained with anti5me C primary antibody (1:4,000 dilution; Calbiochem). The TMA slides were digitally scanned, and the immunohistochemical staining was analyzed using the FrIDA image analysis tool [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] See supplementary materials for a detailed description of evaluation of immunohistochemical staining and quantitative image analysis using FrIDA.",
